{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Cache keys generated from identical query parameters are always identical, and keys from different parameters never collide.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is the key-derivation function itself (canonicalization + hashing). No I/O, subprocess, or model behavior is required. MOCK-MISS is low if we directly test the real key generator implementation; Integration adds little unless key generation is split across modules.","test_description":"Unit-test the real key generator with property-style cases: permuted parameter order, equivalent typed values, null/empty handling, and large random parameter sets. Assert deterministic equality for semantically identical inputs and assert no collisions across a large generated corpus.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The TTL for a cache entry is computed correctly based on the data category's configured freshness rule (e.g., user profiles = 5 minutes, product catalog = 1 hour).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Risk is in module handoff: category -> config lookup -> TTL calculator (and often clock handling). A pure function test can miss miswired config keys/default fallbacks (MOCK-MISS yes). No real network/OS/model dependency is needed.","test_description":"Integration-test TTL computation by wiring real config loading/parsing with the TTL service and a fixed test clock. Verify multiple categories, unknown-category fallback behavior, and unit conversions (minutes/hours) from config into final TTL values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When memory usage exceeds the configured threshold, the eviction strategy switches from LRU to LFU as specified in the configuration.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a coordination behavior across memory-pressure measurement, config threshold evaluation, and strategy selector. A unit test of selector logic alone can miss wiring bugs (MOCK-MISS yes). It does not inherently require OS-level memory metrics if pressure is derived from cache internals.","test_description":"Integration-test with real cache manager components: feed controlled cache growth/pressure signals around the threshold and verify active strategy transitions from LRU to LFU exactly as configured (including boundary conditions at and just above threshold).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A write to the underlying PostgreSQL table invalidates all cache entries whose keys match the affected rows.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears at local data-flow boundary: DB write path -> invalidation hook/listener -> cache key matcher -> cache store. Pure mocks can hide trigger/query-shape/key-mapping defects (MOCK-HIDE yes). Per level defs, local DB wiring is Integration.","test_description":"Integration-test against a local PostgreSQL instance (test DB) plus real cache layer wiring. Seed rows and corresponding cached entries, execute INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE on affected rows, then assert all matching keys are invalidated while unrelated keys remain.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The eviction policy removes the correct entries — least-recently-used under LRU, least-frequently-used under LFU — when the cache is full.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on interaction between access tracking, frequency counters, active policy selection, and storage eviction point. Unit tests of isolated policy functions can miss state-update and handoff bugs (MOCK-MISS yes). No external network/OS/model dependency required.","test_description":"Integration-test the in-memory cache subsystem end-to-end: fill to capacity, run a scripted sequence of gets/puts to create known recency/frequency ordering, trigger eviction, and assert exact evicted keys under LRU and LFU modes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.27,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
